content.description: SDS. match hands on large flake and a good right foot. head up using Right hand to incut , left hand crimp , then make a big move with right hand to a perfect juggy horn . Mantel slightly to the left
content.location: Boulder sits on the top left of zeezus wall directly above the zeezus problem

climbs.name: Don't Tell Me What To Do

content.description: Start matched on crimp flake underneath small bulge, left heel on start hold of Stick that Mantle. Pull off the ground and bump the left hand up a set of two crimps, track the right hand in to the first crimp. Finish on the jug 2-3' right of the finish of Stick That Mantle, I locked on the right crimp and crossed all the way over to the jug with the left hand. Crux may be avoiding the dab on the rock perched right behind you.
content.protection: 1 pad and a spotter would be helpful as there is about 8' of space from the boulder to the edge of the Zeezus wall.
content.location: On the right side of the Zeezus wall prow. Climb up around the Zeezus wall on the left side and then turn back to hop on top of the wall. This 'boulder' is the rock sitting atop the wall that you have to sneak around to get down when doing climbs on the Zeezus wall.

content.description: Above the zeezus wall, consisting of several really interesting  balance boulders
